™’Ł@9a578423116d4e63a78e40820b013f491ae5bafc786b7ead52fb0d3f69bc292eŁrTitle: 
Path: 
Content:
``explore``
Explore is a table pager, just like 
``less``
 but for table structured data.
’Ł@dd97ec8703fb0796ad52abf7c089cbdb7aece1c2a15c2d12fc2983910428197cŁXTitle: Signature
Path: Signature
Content:
``> explore --head --index --reverse --peek``
’Ł@e46b4007ba70e2ace46088e2630bd4ae240086497e37260bf0f5ebbe8fdcb7ecŚ0Title: Signature
Path: Parameters
Content:
``--head {bool}``
: Show or hide column headers (default true)
``--index, -i``
: Show row indexes when viewing a list
``--tail, -t``
: Start with the viewport scrolled to the bottom
``--peek, -p``
: When quitting, output the value of the cell the cursor was on
’Ł@bc1a72402e0eeed2d456abdf8c476c9fd7b9f202f11ab0ad36da371e50b8aed0ŚrTitle: Signature
Path: Get Started
Content:
```Fenced(Borrowed("nu"))
ls | explore -i

```
explore-ls-png
So the main point of 
[link: /commands/docs/explore.md] ``explore``
 is 
``:table``
 (Which you see on the above screenshot).
You can interact with it via 
``<Left>``
, 
``<Right>``
, 
``<Up>``
, 
``<Down>``
 
arrow keys
. It also supports the 
``Vim``
 keybindings 
``<h>``
, 
``<j>``
, 
``<k>``
, and 
``<l>``
, 
``<Ctrl-f>``
 and 
``<Ctrl-b>``
, and it supports the 
``Emacs``
 keybindings 
``<Ctrl-v>``
, 
``<Alt-v>``
, 
``<Ctrl-p>``
, and 
``<Ctrl-n>``
.
You can inspect a underlying values by entering into cursor mode. You can press either 
``<i>``
 or 
``<Enter>``
 to do so.

Then using 
arrow keys
 you can choose a necessary cell.

And you'll be able to see it's underlying structure.
You can obtain more information about the various aspects of it by 
``:help``
.
’Ł@b44697ff89d82af96728dd50dc3a6ad562e9a95504c72c78ece8898520712b3bŚTitle: Signature
Path: Commands
Content:
[link: /commands/docs/explore.md] ``explore``
 has a list of built in commands you can use. Commands are run through pressing 
``<:>``
 and then a command name.
To find out the comprehensive list of commands you can type 
``:help``
.
’Ł@7cbdb43a3a8f9df91657bd11b246028b8e69254b4312a7a4152c7954238dcf10ŚTitle: Signature
Path: Config
Content:
You can configure many things (including styles and colors), via config.

You can find an example configuration in 
[link: https://github.com/nushell/nushell/blob/main/crates/nu-utils/src/default_files/default_config.nu] ``default-config.nu``
.
’Ł@c5f9578580e6457c48ddefcd08d5594466ea063c9c04430e19f97b53b261883eŁuTitle: Signature
Path: Peeking a Value
Content:
```Fenced(Borrowed("nu"))
$nu | explore --peek

```
